
[1]lameness

   LA'MENESS, n.

   1. An impaired state of the body or limbs; loss of natural soundness
   and strength by a wound or by disease; particularly applied to the
   limbs, and implying a total or partial inability; as the lameness of
   the leg or arm.

   2. Imperfection; weakness; as the lameness of an argument or of a
   description.
